oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mount Pleasant First Presbyterian Church
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the exterior of First Presbyterian Church located on Main Street, near the Mount Pleasant public square. Silhouettes of people can be seen in the church courtyard and in the street. A carriage is parked on the left in the foreground.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Churches; People; Streets; Carriages & coaches
